ENTRY            M0545   20260113   20260226   20260226       M143
SUBENT        M0545001   20260113   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                 12         37
TITLE      High-resolution measurement  of  the  12C(gamma,p)11B
            reaction to excited states for Eg = 50 - 70 MeV.
AUTHOR     (A.Kuzin,R.P.Rassool,M.N.Thompson,J.-O.Adler,
            K.Fissum,K.Hansen,L.Isaksson,M.Lundin,B.Nilsson,
            H.Ruijter,B.Schroder,J.R.M.Annand,G.I.Crawford,
            J.C.McGeorge,J.Gregel,J.Ryckebusch)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,58,2167,1998)
INSTITUTE  (3AULAML,2SWDLND,2UK GLS,2BLGGHT)
FACILITY   (MICRT,2SWDLND)
INC-SOURCE (TAGD) Tagged   photon   facility  at  the  MAX  Lab,
            University of Lund.
SAMPLE     Graphite-carbon target with the dimensions of 10 x 10
            cm,  2-mm thick (235 mg/cm2).  The target was placed
            at 25 degree to the beam.
DETECTOR   (TELES,CSICR,SCIN) 7.5-cm-diam.  by  7.5-cm-deep  CsI
            E-crystal,  0.5-mm-thick  NE102 plastic dE-detectors
            for protons.
           (NAICR) 25-cm-diam.,  30-cm-deep  NaI  detectors  for
            decay gammas.
METHOD     (COINC,EDE,GSPEC) Decay  gammas  spectra measurements
            in coincidence with reaction photoprotons.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No    information    about    sources   of
            uncertainties.
COMMENT    Relative population  of  states  in 11B following the
            12C(gamma,p) reaction has  ben  measured  with  high
            resolution    using   the   deexcitation   gamma-ray
            technique.  The states near 7  MeV  in  11B  clearly
            resolved   and  the  measured  population  clarifies
            earlier conflicting data.  Comparison of the results
            with  new  calculations  indicates the importance of
            both one-nucleon and multinucleon processes.
HISTORY    (19990226C)
           (20180301U) Corrected by SD and VV:  Updated  to  new
            date   formats,  lower  case,  AUTHOR,  BIB  updated,
            STATUS.
           (20260113A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: AUTHOR,
            INSTITUTE, EN-SEC, STATUS.
ENDBIB              37
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
    60.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           44
